and what we found was really interesting.

53
00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:06.160
Most of the countries in the European Union have signed up, in fact,

54
00:03:06.360 --> 00:03:10.160
all of them, as far as we can work out, have signed up to the

55
00:03:10.300 --> 00:03:11.920
GDPR.

56
00:03:12.960 --> 00:03:16.700
Hmm. I didn't know what this was either, but it's the General Data

57
00:03:16.940 --> 00:03:20.900
Protection Regulation. So they all sign up to the General Data

58
00:03:20.970 --> 00:03:24.220
Protection Regulation, and this sets strict

59
00:03:24.360 --> 00:03:28.049
regulations which control the surveillance and

60
00:03:28.240 --> 00:03:30.540
storage of people in public places.

61
00:03:31.380 --> 00:03:35.060
For example, there's a proportionality requirement.

62
00:03:35.640 --> 00:03:38.980
Police cannot indiscriminately photograph the entire

63
00:03:39.020 --> 00:03:39.840
population.

64
00:03:41.230 --> 00:03:44.980
The collection of biometric data is prohibited in

65
00:03:45.100 --> 00:03:47.700
principle, but if permitted,

66
00:03:48.100 --> 00:03:51.700
if it's strictly necessary, it must be

67
00:03:51.780 --> 00:03:55.380
proportionate for investigating specific crimes

68
00:03:55.920 --> 00:03:58.200
or maintaining security.

69
